SIMPLE: proembryo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proembryo
<hw>Pro*em"bry*o</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>pro-</ets> + <ets>embryo</ets>. ]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The series of cells formed in the ovule of a flowering
plant after fertilization, but before the formation of the embryo.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The primary growth from the spore in certain
cryptogamous plants; <as>as, the <ex>proembryo</ex>, or protonema, of
mosses</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proemial</ent>⟦br⟧
